This strategy trades Gold (GC) using an Asia session breakout model. It first identifies the high and low of the Asia trading session to establish a range. When price breaks above or below this range during the defined trade window, the strategy enters a position in the direction of the breakout. Optional EMA trend filtering can be used to align trades with the prevailing trend. Risk management includes configurable ATR-based or fixed stop losses and profit targets, along with an optional time-based exit at the end of the session. The strategy is designed for intraday traders looking to capture volatility expansion following the typically tighter Asia session range.
